In a conversation with CalWatchdog.com Editor Brian Calle, San Diego Mayor Kevin Faulconer discusses the importance of preserving the environment and why it should not be a partisan issue. During the interview, Mayor Faulconer highlights the environment as our quality of life and emphasizes the need to preserve the stateâ€™s clean air and water for future generations. He also discusses the steps he has taken as mayor to ensure San Diego is doing its part to reduce greenhouse gas emissions as well as increase the availability of electric charging stations and solar hookups.



